    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In virtute et misericordia omnipotentis Dei. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/21">Berengarius</persName> gratia Dei <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs>. Si fidelium nostrorum peticionibus regalis
                        munificentie effectum inpendimus, devotiores eos ad nostra obsequia reddimus
                        et ad eterne retributionis munera proficere nobis non dubitamus. Quapropter
                        omnium [fidelium] sancte Dei Eclesie nostrorumque presentium scilicet ac
                        futurorum comperiat industria, qualiter <persName
                            key="#Intercessory #Bishops #fidelisOf" ref="#people/369"
                            >Iohannes</persName>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/220">sancte <placeName ref="#places/65"
                                >Ticinensis</placeName> eclesie</orgName> venerabilis <rs
                            key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs> et <persName
                            key="#Intercessory #Marquis/duke #Palatine_count #Consiliarius_regis #fidelisOf"
                            ref="#people/1502">Oldericus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Palatine_count">comes</rs> et <rs key="#Marquis/duke">marchio</rs>
                        sacri palatii nostri <rs key="#Consiliarius_regis">consiliarius</rs>
                        <rs key="#fidelisOf">fideles</rs> nostri suppliciter nostram <rs
                            key="#Intercessory">petierunt</rs> maiestatem, quatinus pro iminenti
                        sevorum Ungrorum vastacione cuidam fideli nostro <persName
                            key="#Other_clerics"><name ref="Leo">Leoni</name></persName> sancte
                            <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/116"><placeName ref="#places/245"
                                >Novariensis</placeName> eclesie</orgName>
                        <rs key="#Other_clerics">vicedomino</rs> in propriis suis rebus finibus
                            <geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/327"><placeName
                                ref="#places/733">Plumbiensis</placeName> commitatus</geogName> in
                        vocabulis, villulis, id sunt <placeName
                            key="#Castle #Defensive_elements #Periodic_markets #Teloneum #Immunity #Right_to_fortify"
                            ref="#places/736">Peronate</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Castle #Defensive_elements #Periodic_markets #Teloneum #Immunity #Right_to_fortify"
                            ref="#places/739">Terdoblade</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Castle #Defensive_elements #Periodic_markets #Teloneum #Immunity #Right_to_fortify"
                            ref="#places/738">Cammari</placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Castle #Defensive_elements #Periodic_markets #Teloneum #Immunity #Right_to_fortify"
                            ref="#places/601">Galiade</placeName>, concederemus <rs
                            key="#Right_to_fortify">licentiam hedificandi castella</rs> necessaria
                        noscuntur, videlicet <rs key="#Defensive_elements">merrulos, fossata,
                            bertiscas atque spizatas</rs>. Quorum petitionem utillimam considerantes
                        ac predicti Leonis fidelitatem animadvertentes, ita fieri annuimus, hoc
                        nostre concessionis pragmaticum scribi iubentes, quo eidem Leoni concedimus
                        licentiam castella hedificandi in predictis locis cum omnibus nocessariis
                        instrumentis superius postulatis, et per hoc largimur <rs
                            key="#Periodic_markets">ei potestatem inibi faciendi annuales
                            mercationes</rs>, et perdonamus omnem publicam reddibitionem omnemque
                            <rs key="#Teloneum">theloneum</rs> vel exibitionem, ut <rs
                            key="#Immunity">nullus rei publice minister habeat licentiam inibi aut
                            ubicumque in eiusdem rebus suiscumque pertinentibus predictam
                            redibitionem vel exibitionem exigere</rs>, sed liceat et siusque
                        heredibus ac proheredibus eadem <rs
                            key="#Castle #Periodic_markets"
                            >castella cum ipsis mercationibus in nostra mercede sine omni publica
                            inquisitione habere, tenere, ac quieto ordine possidere</rs>. Si quis
                        autem contra hoc nostre concessionis preceptum agere temptaverit, sciat se
                        compositurum <rs key="#Penalty">auri optimi libras LX</rs>, medietatem <rs
                            key="#Camera_regis">kamere palatii nostri</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">medietatem sepe dicto Leoni
                            suisque heredibus vel quibus ipse concesserit</rs>.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="editions">
                <p>DD B I, pp. 266-268, n. CII</p>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="additional">
